This bug appears with my small pixelart bmfont. Somehow `at` parameter of `TextField#wordUnderCursor` exceeds text's length by one and that causes crash.

This is workaround for TextField/TextArea I use:

```
@Override
protected int[] wordUnderCursor (int at) {
    String text = this.text;
    // Here is a fix. We constrain at parameter with text length
    int start = Math.min(text.length(), at), right = text.length(), left = 0, index = start;
    for (; index < right; index++) {
        if (!isWordCharacter(text.charAt(index))) {
            right = index;
            break;
        }
    }
    for (index = start - 1; index > -1; index--) {
        if (!isWordCharacter(text.charAt(index))) {
            left = index + 1;
            break;
        }
    }
    return new int[] {left, right};
}
```
